title: Angela Davis interviews Carmen McRae (1977)
description: Jazz singer, composer and actress Carmen McRae (1920 - 1994) talks with activist Angela Davis in San Francisco on November 18, 1977. The interview was recorded around the time of McRae's show at Club Mocambo in San Francisco's Tenderloin district. McRae discusses her early career as a pianist, her approach to performance, women's involvement in show business, and her experiences with Charlie Parker
